<TITLE> Six JU students suspended </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Jahangirnagar University, Apr 5 (bdnews24.com) - Jahangirnagar University suspended six students Sunday in sequel to violent clashes on Friday. Vice chancellor Sharif Enamul Kabir took the decision to suspend them for six months, the university said in a statement said. At least 10 people were injured and some eight dormitory rooms vandalised as two Bangladesh Chhatra League factions fought over control of Mir Mosharraf Hossain Hall. Of the suspended students, Shafiul Mahmood, Arif Iqbal Hossain, Khan Mohammad Abu Sayeer Al-Arabi, KM Taifur Siddiqui were residents of Mir Miosharraf Hossain Hall. Sajidur Rahman and KM Taifur Siddiqui were of Kamal Uddin Hall and Al-Beruni Hall. Police detained all but one, Jihan, on Friday in a raid shortly after the clash. Police took them into remand for a day's interrogation. JU senate meet The JU senate met Sunday over the university's volatile situation with factional clashes of ruling Awami League-backed student front continuing on the campus for weeks. The authorities were tight-lipped about the meeting that ran from 11am to 12:30pm. The vice chancellor told reporters that home minister Sahara Khatun had asked to stay updated about the latest situation on the campus after he had briefed her Friday about the clashes. A syndicate member said the vice chancellor convened the meeting to discuss what should be done about law and order on the campus. bdn
